		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				Couple of thoughts... <br>  <br> My necro is 50 Deathsight, rest in Servant for the extra buff. Now, while he's not just a farming bot type toon, he does farm well. When you can continuously pull mobs w/o ever stopping (at least till you fall asleep), you farm well imho. A lot of people stop at 48 for Sight. I play on Gaheris, so my focus is on PvE of course. That being said, when I go on high level raids, i find that the thing that helps people the most (besides power xfer which is less needed with power fonts), is my lvl 50 spec af debuff. There has been many times when tanks have turned to me and said &quot;Wow, my damage definately jumped a noticeable chunk&quot;. Of course, vs. the truly high level mobs, it doens't make as much of a differance, but vs. knights, hulks, and other such level critters, it is definately a help. I am currently RR 2L5 and have WP 4 and MoM 4. That with a set of ToA armor gets me 400's - 1k damage (with crit)while PV'ing (depending on the mob of course...talking oj+). Can't complain about that.
